<!--
VOICING PLAN:
- Key Bb (2 flats: Bb, Eb). 12-bar form, 4/4. Bb = ①, Eb = ④, F = ⑤, Gm = ③m.
- Non-diatonic: Eø7 → ③m (Gm), D (chrom.) → ① or ③m, Am → ①, C# → ⑤.
- LH open voicings: Bb2-F3-Bb3-D4 standard throughout.
- RH: light thirds and minor sixths, floating above the Bb triad.

VOICE LEADING HIGHLIGHTS:
- RH climbs to Bb5-G5 at bar 9 (highest melodic Eb5-Eb5) for climax.
- LH steady quarter-note harmonic rhythm; each change only moves one or two strings.

TEXTURE ARC:
- Three phrases (bars 1-4, 5-8, 9-12). Climax bar 9. Final Bb cadence bar 12.
-->
